I see the `views` directory doesn't exist yet. I'll create the necessary folder structure and components for the workspace page. Here's my plan:

1. Create `views/workspace` directory with these components:
   - WorkspaceView.vue (main page)
   - components/
     - WorkspaceHeader.vue
     - WorkspaceSidebar.vue 
     - WorkspaceItem.vue
     - CreateModal.vue

2. Structure will follow the reference site with:
   - Top navigation header
   - Left sidebar for navigation
   - Main content area showing workspace items
   - Modal for creating new items

Let me create the main workspace view file first:

<write_to_file>
<path>views/workspace/WorkspaceView.vue</path>
<content>

&lt;template&gt;
  &lt;div class="workspace-container"&gt;
    &lt;WorkspaceHeader /&gt;
    &lt;div class="workspace-content"&gt;
      &lt;WorkspaceSidebar /&gt;
      &lt;main class="workspace-main"&gt;
        &lt;div class="workspace-items"&gt;
          &lt;WorkspaceItem 
            v-for="item in workspaceItems" 
            :key="item.id"
            :item="item"
          /&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/main&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;CreateModal v-if="showCreateModal" @close="showCreateModal = false" /&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/template&gt;

&lt;script setup&gt;
import { ref } from 'vue'
import WorkspaceHeader from './components/WorkspaceHeader.vue'
import WorkspaceSidebar from './components/WorkspaceSidebar.vue'
import WorkspaceItem from './components/WorkspaceItem.vue'
import CreateModal from './components/CreateModal.vue'

const showCreateModal = ref(false)
const workspaceItems = ref([
  {
    id: 1,
    title: 'My First Bot',
    description: 'A helpful assistant',
    icon: '🤖',
    lastEdited: '2 hours ago'
  },
  {
    id: 2,
    title: 'Marketing Bot',
    description: 'Social media content creator',
    icon: '📢',
    lastEdited: '1 day ago'
  }
])
&lt;/script&gt;

&lt;style scoped&gt;
.workspace-container {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  height: 100vh;
}

.workspace-content {
  display: flex;
  flex: 1;
  overflow: hidden;
}

.workspace-main {
  flex: 1;
  padding: 24px;
  overflow-y: auto;
}

.workspace-items {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(280px, 1fr));
  gap: 16px;
}
&lt;/style&gt;

</content>
</write_to_file>

Now I'll create the header component:

<write_to_file>
<path>views/workspace/components/WorkspaceHeader.vue</path>
<content>

&lt;template&gt;
  &lt;header class="workspace-header"&gt;
    &lt;div class="header-left"&gt;
      &lt;h1&gt;My Workspace&lt;/h1&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class="header-right"&gt;
      &lt;button class="create-btn" @click="$emit('create')"&gt;
        + Create
      &lt;/button&gt;
